<dl id="n40101f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40101f">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40101f"> 101(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Despotmania ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Anushirwan (in full Anushinrawin = sweet of soul) is popularly supposed to have begun his rule badly after the fashion of Eastern despots, and presently to have become the justest of monarchs. <small> Richard F. Burton, trans. <a name="RFBS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RFBS"><cite title="source">Supplemental Nights to the Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night with Notes Anthropological and Explanatory</cite></a> (n.d.) xvi.33</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
